The paper proposes a framework for graph traversal in relational database management systems, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the influence of graph topology on traversal execution time, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve machine learning techniques, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed framework compared to native graph database management systems, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SI).
